1436
02:14:54,013 --> 02:14:57,514
She's been an active asset
of ours for some time.

1437
02:15:01,181 --> 02:15:02,514
Until now.

1438
02:15:04,348 --> 02:15:05,764
She loves your son.

1439
02:15:10,681 --> 02:15:13,348
Sometimes
even spies fall in love.

1440
02:15:17,181 --> 02:15:18,931
We can protect him.

1441
02:15:19,432 --> 02:15:20,932
Make him safe.

1442
02:15:21,348 --> 02:15:23,682
Nobody would know,
not even him.

1443
02:15:27,265 --> 02:15:29,849
All it would require
is for you

1444
02:15:31,932 --> 02:15:33,266
to help us

1445
02:15:34,598 --> 02:15:36,598
when your help is needed.

1446
02:15:51,433 --> 02:15:53,266
I thought
you'd like to see this.

1447
02:15:57,766 --> 02:15:59,850
She's a very pretty girl.

1448
02:16:00,933 --> 02:16:03,600
It's easy to see
why he fell for her.

1449
02:16:19,600 --> 02:16:23,017
I know it's an extremely
difficult situation for you.

1450
02:16:27,351 --> 02:16:30,435
But I'm afraid I'm going to
need your answer very soon.

1451
02:16:33,351 --> 02:16:34,851
You must decide

1452
02:16:36,601 --> 02:16:39,101
what is of more importance
to you.

1453
02:16:40,852 --> 02:16:42,518
Your country or...

1454
02:16:47,019 --> 02:16:48,518
Or your son.

1455
02:17:18,769 --> 02:17:20,602
She's not
who you think she is.

1456
02:17:22,853 --> 02:17:25,020
She's not a friendly, Edward.

1457
02:17:25,687 --> 02:17:27,520
I don't believe you.

1458
02:17:27,936 --> 02:17:30,186
Why should I believe you?

1459
02:17:30,520 --> 02:17:33,437
You told me yourself
not to trust anybody.

1460
02:17:34,437 --> 02:17:37,186
You're the master
at creating the truth.

1461
02:17:39,021 --> 02:17:40,437
I love her.

1462
02:17:41,187 --> 02:17:42,854
I've asked her
to marry me.

1463
02:17:43,354 --> 02:17:45,187
I will not let you
take that away from me.

1464
02:17:45,354 --> 02:17:47,604
I can't protect you anymore,
I can't keep you safe.

1465
02:17:47,687 --> 02:17:48,770
Safe?

1466
02:17:51,271 --> 02:17:53,438
Safe? I never felt safe.

1467
02:17:53,688 --> 02:17:54,937
I was always frightened.

1468
02:17:55,021 --> 02:17:58,021
I always lived in fear
that something awful
was going to happen to you.

1469
02:17:58,104 --> 02:18:00,021
Or if not,
to Mother or to me.

1470
02:18:00,021 --> 02:18:03,187
I was always afraid, because
everything was a secret.

1471
02:19:22,357 --> 02:19:23,357
Edward.

1472
02:19:23,441 --> 02:19:25,774
Hello, may I come in?
Yes. Of course.

1473
02:19:25,858 --> 02:19:27,774
Is everything all right?

1474
02:19:28,858 --> 02:19:30,524
I was on my way home
from work

1475
02:19:30,608 --> 02:19:33,858
and I had this
overwhelming desire
to hear you play the violin.

1476
02:19:33,858 --> 02:19:35,525
Play the violin? But...

1477
02:19:36,691 --> 02:19:39,609
Edward, I'm so tired.
Can't this wait
until tomorrow?

1478
02:19:39,858 --> 02:19:42,192
I'd appreciate it
if you'd play it now.

1479
02:19:43,442 --> 02:19:44,525
Now?

1480
02:22:58,699 --> 02:23:01,367
I just wanted to
hear something from you
that was true.

1481
02:23:11,617 --> 02:23:13,283
<i>He was careless.</i>

1482
02:23:13,700 --> 02:23:16,283
FBI. You're under arrest.
Stand up.

1483
02:23:18,200 --> 02:23:20,200
Didn't learn how to
hide in plain sight.

1484
02:23:20,533 --> 02:23:22,367
Where are they taking me?

1485
02:23:22,450 --> 02:23:25,367
I can't go home! You know
they can't trust me anymore!

1486
02:23:25,867 --> 02:23:27,700
You know
what they will do to me!

1487
02:23:28,034 --> 02:23:29,368
Sorry, Edward.

1488
02:23:30,867 --> 02:23:33,242
<i>I truly did like you.</i>

1489
02:23:34,700 --> 02:23:38,660
<i>I mean it. In another world,
we actually would have been
quite good friends.</i>

1490
02:23:42,034 --> 02:23:43,868
Are you still there, Mother?

1491
02:23:44,034 --> 02:23:46,368
Your worst fear has come true.

1492
02:23:50,868 --> 02:23:52,701
<i>Alone and friendless</i>

1493
02:23:54,785 --> 02:23:56,952
<i>without a country of your own.</i>

1494
02:25:09,204 --> 02:25:12,038
We have a whole new place
to fight over.

1495
02:25:14,247 --> 02:25:15,538
The stars.

1496
02:25:20,455 --> 02:25:21,871
Your offer.

1497
02:25:25,455 --> 02:25:27,038
I have to decline.

1498
02:25:38,039 --> 02:25:41,872
You've succeeded
in stopping us
from taking back Cuba.

1499
02:25:45,580 --> 02:25:47,373
The damage is done.

1500
02:25:50,456 --> 02:25:52,832
There's no need for you
to hurt my son.

1501
02:25:59,373 --> 02:26:01,623
Let's just leave it
between you and me.

1502
02:26:06,040 --> 02:26:07,414
Very well.

1503
02:26:09,374 --> 02:26:10,748
I will wait.

1504
02:26:12,873 --> 02:26:14,915
But there will come a time

1505
02:26:16,873 --> 02:26:19,624
when I will ask you to help me
with a problem

1506
02:26:20,707 --> 02:26:24,624
that wouldn't cost you much
but be of some value to me.

1507
02:26:28,290 --> 02:26:30,874
You never know
what the future will bring.

1508
02:26:33,499 --> 02:26:36,749
Friends can be enemies,
and enemies friends.

1509
02:26:53,625 --> 02:26:54,959
This girl,

1510
02:26:57,291 --> 02:26:59,875
neither of us
can be sure about her.

1511
02:27:03,667 --> 02:27:06,626
But she's about to be
a part of your family.

1512
02:27:09,376 --> 02:27:11,167
I believe in family.

1513
02:27:16,459 --> 02:27:19,292
You want her to be
a part of your family,

1514
02:27:20,876 --> 02:27:22,210
don't you?

1515
02:27:47,210 --> 02:27:49,211
It was good to see you.

1516
02:27:51,585 --> 02:27:55,211
We will talk again,
my dear friend.

1517
02:28:03,877 --> 02:28:05,211
Sorry to bother.

1518
02:28:05,294 --> 02:28:08,461
I want to buy a little
souvenir to my daughter.
They have no change.

1519
02:28:10,128 --> 02:28:11,378
What does it cost?

1520
02:28:11,420 --> 02:28:12,878
It costs a dollar.

1521
02:28:14,878 --> 02:28:18,670
Here. It's a gift.
Regards from
the United States government.

1522
02:28:19,753 --> 02:28:22,545
It's a cardinal rule
to be generous in a democracy.

1523
02:28:27,629 --> 02:28:28,878
Thank you.

1524
02:29:22,797 --> 02:29:24,506
<i>So where is she?</i>

1525
02:29:24,631 --> 02:29:26,381
<i>We're gonna meet her
at the church.</i>

1526
02:29:26,423 --> 02:29:29,381
I can't wait to meet her.
You'll love her.
You're gonna love her.

1527
02:29:32,298 --> 02:29:33,965
Yes, that's good.

1528
02:29:49,215 --> 02:29:50,549
Come on in.

1529
02:29:59,799 --> 02:30:01,382
Hello, Margaret.

1530
02:30:05,924 --> 02:30:08,716
Let's celebrate.
I'll get some champagne.

1531
02:30:16,049 --> 02:30:17,800
How was the flight?

1532
02:30:20,216 --> 02:30:21,633
It was long.

1533
02:30:31,466 --> 02:30:33,800
How do you like
living in Phoenix?

1534
02:30:37,551 --> 02:30:39,634
It's the first time
I've slept in years.

1535
02:30:44,134 --> 02:30:45,467
Here we go.

1536
02:31:11,135 --> 02:31:12,468
To your happiness.

1537
02:31:12,719 --> 02:31:14,051
To your happiness.

1538
02:33:01,473 --> 02:33:02,890
Your wife...

1539
02:33:03,389 --> 02:33:05,181
What have you done?

1540
02:33:06,890 --> 02:33:09,140
Will you go inside, Mother?

1541
02:33:10,639 --> 02:33:12,307
Go inside, Mom.

1542
02:33:14,057 --> 02:33:16,598
Please, just go in the church.

1543
02:33:26,807 --> 02:33:28,474
She's pregnant.

1544
02:33:46,891 --> 02:33:48,725
You couldn't...
You couldn't have.

1545
02:33:50,224 --> 02:33:51,892
You couldn't.
No.

1546
02:33:52,892 --> 02:33:54,558
I love you.

1547
02:33:55,558 --> 02:33:57,350
I love you
so much.

1548
02:34:21,893 --> 02:34:23,643
- Mr. Wilson?
- Mr. Hayes.

1549
02:34:24,726 --> 02:34:27,226
Have you been here before,
Mother?
No, I haven't.

1550
02:34:28,226 --> 02:34:30,143
Whose idea was that?

1551
02:34:30,392 --> 02:34:32,060
It's classified.

1552
02:34:35,060 --> 02:34:37,726
Mr. Allen has notified
the President he'll resign.

1553
02:34:39,809 --> 02:34:42,393
<i>Something about
Swiss bank accounts.</i>

1554
02:34:44,226 --> 02:34:45,560
Where did these
come from?

